-- Dubai to Triple Tourism Revenue to 300 Billion Dirhams by 2020
-- B y   S t e f a n i a   B i a n c h i
-- 2013-05-05T05:49:51Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-05-05/dubai-to-triple-tourism-revenue-to-300-billion-dirhams-by-2020.html
Dubai plans to double the number of
visitors to 20 million by 2020 and triple annual revenue from
the industry to 300 billion dirhams ($82 billion).  The emirate’s ruler, Sheikh Mohammed bin Rashid al-Maktoum,
yesterday approved the “Dubai Vision for Tourism” program to
build developments and infrastructure, according to an e-mailed
statement from the government.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Stefania Bianchi in Dubai at 
 sbianchi10@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
